  "content_markdown": "Version: 8.0\nOn this page\nLevel: beginner\nnote\nThis functionality is available for Creatio 8.0.5 and later.\nYou can specify the objects and records to synchronize with the offline mode of the mobile app. For example, this lets you select the records of existing objects. To do this:\n1. Set up the app in the Mobile Application Wizard. Learn more in a separate guide: [Mobile app setup](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/8.x/no-code-customization/8.0/category/mobile-app-setup).\n2. Click ![](https://academy.creatio.com/sites/default/files/documentation/sdk/ru/BPMonlineWebSDK/Screenshots/TryIt/scr_system_designer.png) to open the System Designer.\n3. Open the **System setup** block \u2192 **Mobile application wizard**.\n4. Open the workplace whose synchronization settings to change, for example, **Main workplace**.\n5. Click **Actions** \u2192 **Set up synchronization** on the toolbar. This opens the **Mobile synchronization settings** page.\nThe page contains the list of objects the workplace uses (Fig. 1). For example, sections, lookups, details, etc.\nFig. 1 Opening the Mobile synchronization settings page\n![Fig.\u00a01 Opening the Mobile synchronization settings page](https://academy.creatio.com/sites/default/files/documentation/sdk/ru/BPMonlineWebSDK/Screenshots/SetUpMobileAppSynchronization/8.0/scr_process_of_opening_the_pages.gif)\nCreatio adds an object to the **Mobile synchronization settings** page once you add and set up the corresponding object on the Mobile Creatio app page using **Mobile Application Wizard**. For example, add and set up \"Product in order\" detail to add the \"Product in order\" object to the **Mobile synchronization settings** page.\n6. Select an object whose synchronization settings to change.\n7. Change the object synchronization settings. You can turn the synchronization on or off for the entire object or filter records to synchronize (Fig. 2).\nFig. 2 Filter settings for the Activity object\n![Fig.\u00a02 Filter settings for the Activity object](https://academy.creatio.com/sites/default/files/documentation/sdk/ru/BPMonlineWebSDK/Screenshots/SetUpMobileAppSynchronization/8.0/scr_filter_settings.png)\n8. Click **Save**.\n9. Review the synchronized records. You can view the record number of a synchronized object in the **Filtered records count** column or synchronize an app on a mobile device and check.\n* * *\n## See also\u200b\n[Mobile app setup](https://academy.creatio.com/docs/8.x/no-code-customization/8.0/category/mobile-app-setup)",
